## Issues Found

### Non-blocking (minor API quirks)
1. **POST returns `ids` array instead of `id` scalar** — `{"ids":[53],"ok":true}`. The UI handles this correctly, but the API design is inconsistent with REST conventions. Does not affect UI or user workflow.
2. **GET /clientfinder/leads/\<id\> returns 405** — No single-resource GET route; the UI fetches from the paginated list endpoint instead, so no UI impact. Route could be added for completeness.

### False negatives in initial test
- Row click selects checkbox (expected). Drill-down opens via "View details" eye button (`[title="View details"]`), not the row body. UI behavior is intentional and correct per the screenshot.
- work-samples route returns HTTP 404 from GH Pages — expected SPA behavior; 404.html redirects to React router which renders the iframe. Documented in deploy.out as not a defect.

---

## Visual Verification

Screenshot taken at drill-down modal open confirmed:
- Company header (name, industry tag, city/state, employee count)
- Homepage screenshot placeholder (with URL + "Screenshot captured during scrape" label)
- Detected stack issues (pill tags: Legacy WordPress, Non-responsive layout, Outdated jQuery)
- Contact info panel (email, phone, contact form link)
- Technical Audit Score section with animated progress bars
- Key Decision Maker card (avatar, name, title, seniority badge, Apollo badge, LinkedIn link)
- Outreach section with status dropdown and notes textarea

Demo design is bespoke dark CRM aesthetic, no portfolio site styles. All 10/10 richness target features present.

